rcMltMib.name: rcMltMib

revisions.description: Version 22: Added rcStatMltUtilTable.
Version 21: Added rcMltEntryOwner, rcMltDatapathProgrammingState to rcMltTable.

Version 20: Increased MLT ID range for rcStatMltIfExtnMltId, rcStatMltEtherMltId. rcMltId, rcMltSmltId. Added: rcMltPeerPortMembers, rcMltCpLimitPktRate, rcMltCpLimitShutDownEnable, rcMltVlanIdList to rcMltTable. Added: synchronizeInProgress(11) to rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState.
Version 19: Added rcMltDisablePortsOnShutdown.
Version 18: Added rcStatSmltLacpInfoRxMsgCnt, rcStatSmltLacpInfoTxMsgCnt.
Version 17: Added rcMltMtu, rcMltInterfaceType, rcMltConfiguredMembers, rcMltMtuAdminState.
Version 16: Added rcMltAggMinLink, rcMltNotificationObjects, rcMltAggTrapEvent

Version 15: Added rcMltEgressCosProfileName, rcMltEgressPolicerAdminState, rcMltAggrEgressBandwidth, rcMltAggrIngressBandwidth, rcMltAggrMacAlloc Modified rcMltLoadDistributionOption and rcMltUniAggrMacIdx
Version 14: Added rcMltLoadDistributionOption, rcMltUniAggrMacIdx, rcMltUniAggrMacAddress and rcMltQinqEtherType to rcMltTable. Added rcMltBvidPortTable
Version 13: Changed range of rcMltSmltId to 0..256.
Version 12: Changed rcMltEnable from read-only to read-create. Changed all read-write objects in rcMltTable to read-create.
Version 11: Increased to rcMltId & rcMltSmltId from 32 to 256
Version 10: Added enumerations to rcMltDistributionAlgorithm.
Version 9: Fixed range of rcMltVlanIds, allow rcMltIfIndex to be 0.
Version 8: Changed the SYNTAX for rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInUtil & rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutUtil to Gauge32
Version 7: Made Index rcStatMltIfUtilMltId as not-accessible
Version 6: Added rcStatMltIfUtilTable
Version 5: Import MacAddress type
Version 4: Added rcMltVlacpTable
Version 3: Added rcMltVlacpTable

rcStatMltIfExtnTable.name: rcStatMltIfExtnTable
rcStatMltIfExtnTable.description: A table used to store Mlt interface statistics.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets delivered by this MLT to a higher MLT that were not addressed to a nulticast or broadcase address at this sublayer.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt.description: The number of packets delivered to this MLT that were addressed to a nulticast address at this sublayer. For a MAC layer protocol, this number includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt.description: The number of packets delivered to this MLT that were addressed to a broadcast address at this sublayer.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts.description: The number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted that were not addressed to a multicast address at this MLT. This total number includes those packets discarded or unsent.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast.description: The total number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted, and that were addressed to a multicast address at this MLT, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this number includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast.description: The total number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted, and that were addressed to a broadcase address at this MLT, including those that were discarded or not sent.

rcStatMltEtherTable.name: rcStatMltEtherTable
rcStatMltEtherTable.description: A table used to store Mlt Ethernet statistics.

rcStatMltEtherMltId.name: rcStatMltEtherMltId
rcStatMltEtherMltId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Multi-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors.name: rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors
rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular MLT that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors.name: rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors
rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on an MLT that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames.name: rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames
rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular MLT for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this objects is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and it not counted by the corresponding instance of the MultipleCollisionFrames object.

rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames.name: rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames
rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular MLT for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the SingleCollisionFrames objects.

rcStatMltEtherSQETestError.name: rcStatMltEtherSQETestError
rcStatMltEtherSQETestError.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular MLT. SQE stands for Signal Quality Error.

rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss.name: rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss
rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular MLT is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions.name: rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions
rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular MLT later than 512 bit-times (64 octets) into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 mb/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis.name: rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis
rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular MLT fails due to excessive collisions.

rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError.name: rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError
rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular MLT fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the LateCollisions object, the ExcessiveCollisions object, or the CarrierSenseError object.

rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError.name: rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError
rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular MLT. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong.name: rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong
rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong.description: A count of frames received on a particular MLT that exceed the maximum permitted size (1518 octets). The count represented by an instance os this object is incremented when the frame TooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError.name: rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError
rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular MLT fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the FrameTooLongs object, the AlignmentErrors object, of the FCSErrors objects. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of receive errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

rcStatMltIfUtilTable.name: rcStatMltIfUtilTable
rcStatMltIfUtilTable.description: A table used to store Mlt interface utilization.

rcStatMltIfUtilMltId.name: rcStatMltIfUtilMltId
rcStatMltIfUtilMltId.description: To assign an Id within the range specified to the Mlt created

rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInOctets.name: rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInOctets
rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInUtil.name: rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInUtil
rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCInUtil.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this interval, in percent.

rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutOctets.name: rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutOctets
rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutUtil.name: rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutUtil
rcStatMltIfUtilIfHCOutUtil.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this interval, in percent.

rcStatMltUtilTable.name: rcStatMltUtilTable
rcStatMltUtilTable.description: A table used to store statistics for MLT members utilization.

rcStatMltUtilEntry.name: rcStatMltUtilEntry
rcStatMltUtilEntry.description: An entry for MLT members utilization statistics table.

rcStatMltUtilTrafficType.name: rcStatMltUtilTrafficType
rcStatMltUtilTrafficType.description: Type of traffic for one MLT port interface.

rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast5Min.name: rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast5Min
rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast5Min.description: This object returns the percentage of traffic on one MLT port interface for the last 5 minutes.

rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast30Min.name: rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast30Min
rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast30Min.description: This object returns the percentage of traffic on one MLT port interface for the last 30 minutes.

rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast1Hour.name: rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast1Hour
rcStatMltUtilTrafficLast1Hour.description: This object returns the percentage of traffic on one MLT port interface for the last hour.

rcMltNumMlts.name: rcMltNumMlts
rcMltNumMlts.description: The number of MLTs currently defined in the switch.

rcMltPotentialMembers.name: rcMltPotentialMembers
rcMltPotentialMembers.description: The set of ports that are not members of any MLT.

rcMltDisablePortsOnShutdown.name: rcMltDisablePortsOnShutdown
rcMltDisablePortsOnShutdown.description: When true(1), the port members of an MLT will be automatically shutdown when the MLT becomes disabled.

rcMltTable.name: rcMltTable
rcMltTable.description: A list of Multi-Link Trunk entries. The number of entries is given by rcMltNumMlts.

rcMltEntry.name: rcMltEntry
rcMltEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular Multi-Link Trunk.

rcMltId.name: rcMltId
rcMltId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Multi-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcMltName.name: rcMltName
rcMltName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this MLT.

rcMltPortMembers.name: rcMltPortMembers
rcMltPortMembers.description: The set of ports that are members of this MLT.

rcMltPortType.name: rcMltPortType
rcMltPortType.description: The type of MLT port: access(1) or trunk(2).

rcMltNumVlanIds.name: rcMltNumVlanIds
rcMltNumVlanIds.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN IDs that are stored in the rcMltVlanIds variable.

rcMltVlanIds.name: rcMltVlanIds
rcMltVlanIds.description: An array used to identify which VLANs this MLT is associated with. Each VLAN ID is stored as a two octet value. The first octet in the pair holds bits 15-8 of the VLAN ID, while the second octet holds bits 7-0 of the VLAN ID.

rcMltRowStatus.name: rcMltRowStatus
rcMltRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcMltTable.

rcMltIfIndex.name: rcMltIfIndex
rcMltIfIndex.description: Used to indicate the 'logical' ifIndex assigned to this MLT.

rcMltAggregatable.name: rcMltAggregatable
rcMltAggregatable.description: Enable/Disable link aggregation on a MLT.

rcMltClearLinkAggregate.name: rcMltClearLinkAggregate
rcMltClearLinkAggregate.description: clear link aggregate, equivalent to disable and re-enable aggregatable on the MLT.

rcMltNtStgEnable.name: rcMltNtStgEnable
rcMltNtStgEnable.description: Indicates whether this MLT is operating in Nortel Mode or in Cisco Mode. true = Nortel Mode false = Cisco Mode.

rcMltDesignatedPort.name: rcMltDesignatedPort
rcMltDesignatedPort.description: Indicates the Designated port for the MLT.

rcMltAggOperState.name: rcMltAggOperState
rcMltAggOperState.description: Link aggregation state on a MLT.

rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange.name: rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange
rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange.description: The time value since the interface entered its current operational state.

rcMltVplsMgmtVlan.name: rcMltVplsMgmtVlan
rcMltVplsMgmtVlan.description: Management Vlan is configured on this mlt

rcMltLoadDistributionOption.name: rcMltLoadDistributionOption
rcMltLoadDistributionOption.description: Used to specify the Load Balancing option for MLT in UNI

rcMltUniAggrMacIdx.name: rcMltUniAggrMacIdx
rcMltUniAggrMacIdx.description: Used to specify the index of the mac address pool reserved for MLT uni

rcMltUniAggrMacAddress.name: rcMltUniAggrMacAddress
rcMltUniAggrMacAddress.description: Used to display the mac address reserved for this MLT

rcMltQinqEtherType.name: rcMltQinqEtherType
rcMltQinqEtherType.description: The qinq ether type value. It should be displayed and input as Hex value. It would only be used when MLT is associated with QnQ service UNI. Otherwise, it would be ignored

rcMltEgressCosProfileName.name: rcMltEgressCosProfileName
rcMltEgressCosProfileName.description: Mlt Egress COS Profile Name, which is defined by rcCosProfileTable

rcMltAggrEgressBandwidth.name: rcMltAggrEgressBandwidth
rcMltAggrEgressBandwidth.description: Aggregated Egress Bandwidth Policer is used.

rcMltAggrIngressBandwidth.name: rcMltAggrIngressBandwidth
rcMltAggrIngressBandwidth.description: Aggregated Ingress Bandwidth Policer is used.

rcMltAggMinLink.name: rcMltAggMinLink
rcMltAggMinLink.description: If number of active links goes below configured minimum-link number, the entire LAG is declared down.

rcMltInterfaceType.name: rcMltInterfaceType
rcMltInterfaceType.description: This value indicates whether ports in the mlt are of type <normal/silent/uni>. A port can be included in any EVPN service only if this attribute is set to uni. If the port is not part of any VLAN the interface-type is set to silent. Before adding a port to a VLAN the interface type should be changed to normal.

rcMltConfiguredMembers.name: rcMltConfiguredMembers
rcMltConfiguredMembers.description: The set of ports that are configured members of this MLT. Toronto release allows us to add a port to a LACP enabled MLT. These port get added as ConfiguredMembers

rcMltMtuAdminState.name: rcMltMtuAdminState
rcMltMtuAdminState.description: Set Mlt MTU enable or disable

rcMltPeerPortMembers.name: rcMltPeerPortMembers
rcMltPeerPortMembers.description: The set of Peer ports which are connected to local ports (rcMltPortMember) of this MLT

rcMltCpLimitPktRate.name: rcMltCpLimitPktRate
rcMltCpLimitPktRate.description: Used to limit Control packets on the port to qos-levels 6 and 7. Sets the limit in packets per second.

rcMltCpLimitShutDownEnable.name: rcMltCpLimitShutDownEnable
rcMltCpLimitShutDownEnable.description: Used to indicate if the mlt-ports should be shutdown when the CpLimitPktRate is exceeded.

rcMltVlanIdList.name: rcMltVlanIdList
rcMltVlanIdList.description: This bitfield is used to identify which VLANs this MLT is associated with. Each VLAN ID is stored as a bit. The most-significant (left-most) bit represents Vlan Id 1.

rcMltEntryOwner.name: rcMltEntryOwner
rcMltEntryOwner.description: Defines the owner of the MLT.

rcMltDatapathProgrammingState.name: rcMltDatapathProgrammingState
rcMltDatapathProgrammingState.description: Defines the datapath programming state of the MLT.

rcMltMcastDistributionEnable.name: rcMltMcastDistributionEnable
rcMltMcastDistributionEnable.description: Used to enable/disable this feature to distribute multicast traffic on MLT ports. All the cards in the system must be E-Tickets. Cannot perform distribution in a mixed mode.

rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask.name: rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask
rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask.description: Group Mask. Create a MLT abstraction layer to distribute traffic basd on (source, group) information of the multicast packet. The algorithm to pick the actual port nedds to generate a fairly random number for different combinations but a lways generate the same number for a given (source, group) pair. By default, the number of active ports of the MLT is used to MOD the pseudo-random number generated by the XOR of each byte of the masked group address with the masked source address.

rcSltPortTable.name: rcSltPortTable
rcSltPortTable.description: Table containing config info for SLT

rcSltPortEntry.name: rcSltPortEntry
rcSltPortEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular Multi-Link Trunk.

rcSltPortSmltId.name: rcSltPortSmltId
rcSltPortSmltId.description: A uniquely identifies the Single-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcSltPortOperType.name: rcSltPortOperType
rcSltPortOperType.description: The current operate type of the port normal or smlt.

rcSltPortRowStatus.name: rcSltPortRowStatus
rcSltPortRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries of the Table.

rcMltVlacpEntry.name: rcMltVlacpEntry
rcMltVlacpEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular port

rcMltVlacpAdminEnable.name: rcMltVlacpAdminEnable
rcMltVlacpAdminEnable.description: Administratively enable/disable Virtual LACP on a MLT

rcMltVlacpFastPeriodicTimer.name: rcMltVlacpFastPeriodicTimer
rcMltVlacpFastPeriodicTimer.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using Short Timeouts

rcMltVlacpTimeoutScale.name: rcMltVlacpTimeoutScale
rcMltVlacpTimeoutScale.description: Scalar value used to calculate timeout time from periodic time. Timeout = PeriodicTime * TimeoutScale

rcMltVlacpEtherMacAddress.name: rcMltVlacpEtherMacAddress
rcMltVlacpEtherMacAddress.description: Multicast Mac Address exclusively used for VLACPDU's

rcMltVlacpDualHomingEnable.name: rcMltVlacpDualHomingEnable
rcMltVlacpDualHomingEnable.description: Enable/Disable Dual homing on Virtual LACP on a MLT

rcMltBvidPortTable.name: rcMltBvidPortTable
rcMltBvidPortTable.description: Table contains Bridge Vlan configured information for Primary and Secondary ports for MLT-UNI

rcMltBvidPortEntry.name: rcMltBvidPortEntry
rcMltBvidPortEntry.description: Entry with Info about VLAN with its Primary and secondary ports for MLT-UNI

rcMltBvidMltId.name: rcMltBvidMltId
rcMltBvidMltId.description: VLAN ID of the Port List

rcMltBvidVlanId.name: rcMltBvidVlanId
rcMltBvidVlanId.description: VLAN ID of the Port List

rcMltBvidPrimaryPort.name: rcMltBvidPrimaryPort
rcMltBvidPrimaryPort.description: Primary port of the MLT for the VLAN when load distribution option is b-vid

rcMltBvidSecondaryPort.name: rcMltBvidSecondaryPort
rcMltBvidSecondaryPort.description: Secondary port of the MLT for the VLAN when load distribution option is b-vid

rcMltBvidRowStatus.name: rcMltBvidRowStatus
rcMltBvidRowStatus.description: Used to Add/delete entries in the table

rcMltAggTrapEvent.name: rcMltAggTrapEvent
rcMltAggTrapEvent.description: Three trap events type: local down(1), remote down(2), up(3).

rcLinkFlapDetectAutoPortDownEnable.name: rcLinkFlapDetectAutoPortDownEnable
rcLinkFlapDetectAutoPortDownEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the Link Flap Detect feature. When enabled this feature will monitor the number of times a port goes down during a certain interval. If the number exceeds a given bound the port will be forced out-of-service.

rcLinkFlapDetectSendTrap.name: rcLinkFlapDetectSendTrap
rcLinkFlapDetectSendTrap.description: Used to configure whether a trap should be sent if the port is forced out-of-service.

rcLinkFlapDetectFrequency.name: rcLinkFlapDetectFrequency
rcLinkFlapDetectFrequency.description: Used to configure the number of times the port can go down.

rcLinkFlapDetectInterval.name: rcLinkFlapDetectInterval
rcLinkFlapDetectInterval.description: Used to configure the interval (in minutes).

rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState.name: rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState
rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState.description: Indicate the Ha-CPU state. initialization - indicate the CPU is in this state. oneWayActive - Modules that need to be synchronized have registered with the framework (either locally or a message was received from remote CPU (1). twoWayActive - Modules that need to be synchronized have registered with the framework (either locally or a message was received from remote CPU (2). synchronized - Table based synchroniztion was completed on the current CPU (3). remoteIncompatible - CPUs framework version is incompatible with the remote CPU (4). error - If an invalid event is generated in a given state the CPU enters Error state (5). disabled - High Availability is not enabled (6). peerNotConnected - no peer connection is established (7). peerConnected - peer connection is established (8). lostPeerConnection - lost connection to peer/Standby CPU (9). notSynchronized - Table Sync is not complete (10). synchronizeInProgress - Table Sync is in progress (11).

rcL2RedundancyHaEvent.name: rcL2RedundancyHaEvent
rcL2RedundancyHaEvent.description: Indicate the Ha event status. restart (0) - Causes the state machine to restart systemRegistrationDone (1)- Causes the CPU to transfer to One Way or Two Way Active state. Locally or message received from remote CPU. tableSynchronizationDone (2) - Causes the CPU to transfer to Synchronized state. versionIncompatible (3) - Causes the CPU to go to Remote Incompatible state noEvent (4) - Means no event has occured uptill now.

rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu.name: rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu
rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu.description: Indicate if the L2 Redundancy is enabled on the standby CPU.
